data.text:
I haven′t slept, but I'm not tired It′s 4 a.m., a moonless night is alive My head is clear, the morning is fresh It's good to be awake like this It feels like it's been light for years My eyes wide to the dark of this hotel room And an open window above a parking lot Prolific motion, I forgot Nameless places, they are all the same Nameless faces I will not remember You are on my mind again With poetry and rhyme It′s as if you′re still here with me After all this time It's been a while since I recall And now I′m flooded and miles away The sleeping beauty in my heart concealed Awakens now to the kiss of the wind Nameless places, they are all the same Nameless faces I will not remember You are on my mind again With poetry and rhyme It's as if you′re still here with me After all this time 'Cause I′d give the world to be home tonight But the road is long and it pulls me away I miss you deep, and there's no relieve from this steady ache Nameless places, it never seems to end Nameless faces, when all I want is you Writer(s): Sandra Mccracken
